Here is the full picture. Note an important correction to the premise: **"turnout" is not the same generic component as "points"** — it's a completely separate, unrelated table (`Turnout`), not a `TableName` variant. The Paper/collapse-expand treatment currently lives only in `RecordsTable`, which is used for `points`/`averages`/`stalwart`/`speedy`/`pub` (via `YearTable` or directly). If you want turnout to get the same treatment, you'll need to either add it to `Turnout.tsx` separately, or fold turnout into `RecordsTable`'s pattern (it isn't part of the `TableName` enum at all).

## 1. Points table: collapse/expand + Paper treatment

**File:** `/Volumes/Development/next-www-toastboy/src/components/RecordsTable/RecordsTable.tsx`

Full source (154 lines):

```tsx
1  'use client';
2  
3  import {
4      Button,
5      Divider,
6      Paper,
7      Table,
8      TableTbody,
9      TableTd,
10     TableTh,
11     TableThead,
12     TableTr,
13     Title,
14     type TitleOrder,
15     VisuallyHidden,
16 } from '@mantine/core';
17 import { useDisclosure } from '@mantine/hooks';
18 import { IconChevronDown, IconChevronUp } from '@tabler/icons-react';
19 import { type TableName, TableNameSchema } from 'prisma/zod/schemas';
20 import { useId, useMemo } from 'react';
21 
22 import { PlayerLink } from '@/components/PlayerLink/PlayerLink';
23 import { TableScore } from '@/components/TableScore/TableScore';
24 import { config } from '@/lib/config';
25 import { PlayerRecordDataType } from '@/types';
26 
27 export interface Props {
28     table: TableName;
29     year: number;
30     records: PlayerRecordDataType[];
31     title?: string;
32     titleOrder?: TitleOrder;
33 }
34 
35 const rankFieldByTable = {
36     [TableNameSchema.enum.points]: 'rankPoints',
37     [TableNameSchema.enum.averages]: 'rankAverages',
38     [TableNameSchema.enum.stalwart]: 'rankStalwart',
39     [TableNameSchema.enum.speedy]: 'rankSpeedy',
40     [TableNameSchema.enum.pub]: 'rankPub',
41 } satisfies Record<TableName, keyof PlayerRecordDataType>;
42 
43 type RankField = (typeof rankFieldByTable)[TableName];
44 
45 const scoreHeadingByTable = {
46     [TableNameSchema.enum.points]: 'Points',
47     [TableNameSchema.enum.averages]: 'Average',
48     [TableNameSchema.enum.stalwart]: 'Games Played',
49     [TableNameSchema.enum.speedy]: 'Average Response Time (hh:mm:ss)',
50     [TableNameSchema.enum.pub]: 'Pub Score',
51 } satisfies Record<TableName, string>;
52 
53 interface RankDisplay {
54     text: string;
55     visible: boolean;
56 }
57 
58 const rankDisplays = (records: PlayerRecordDataType[], rankField: RankField): RankDisplay[] => {
59     const displays: RankDisplay[] = [];
60     let prevRank: number | null | undefined;
61 
62     for (const record of records) {
63         const rank = record[rankField];
64         const isMissing = rank === null || rank === undefined;
65 
66         displays.push({
67             text: isMissing ? '-' : `${rank}`,
68             visible: isMissing || rank !== prevRank,
69         });
70 
71         prevRank = rank;
72     }
73 
74     return displays;
75 };
76 
77 // Extends the initial page of rows forward past any tie straddling the cutoff,
78 // so a group of equally-ranked players is never split across the toggle.
79 const visibleRowCount = (ranks: RankDisplay[], initial: number): number => {
80     let count = Math.min(initial, ranks.length);
81 
82     while (count < ranks.length && !ranks[count].visible) {
83         count++;
84     }
85 
86     return count;
87 };
88 
89 export const RecordsTable = ({ table, year, records, title, titleOrder = 2 }: Props) => {
90     const rankField = rankFieldByTable[table];
91     const scoreHeading = scoreHeadingByTable[table];
92     const ranks = useMemo(() => rankDisplays(records, rankField), [records, rankField]);
93     const cutoff = useMemo(
94         () => visibleRowCount(ranks, config.recordsTableVisibleRows),
95         [ranks],
96     );
97     const [opened, { toggle }] = useDisclosure(false);
98     const hiddenCount = records.length - cutoff;
99     const visibleRecords = opened ? records : records.slice(0, cutoff);
100    const tbodyId = useId();
101
102    return (
103        <Paper p="sm" miw="14rem" maw="24rem" withBorder>
104            {title ? (
105                <>
106                    <Title order={titleOrder} mb="xs" w="100%" ta="center">{title}</Title>
107                    <Divider mb="xs" />
108                </>
109            ) : null}
110            <Table stickyHeader stickyHeaderOffset={0}>
111                <TableThead>
112                    <TableTr bd="0">
113                        <TableTh p={0}><VisuallyHidden>Position</VisuallyHidden></TableTh>
114                        <TableTh p={0}><VisuallyHidden>Player</VisuallyHidden></TableTh>
115                        <TableTh p={0}><VisuallyHidden>{scoreHeading}</VisuallyHidden></TableTh>
116                    </TableTr>
117                </TableThead>
118                <TableTbody id={tbodyId}>
119                    {visibleRecords.map((record, index) => (
120                        <TableTr
121                            key={record.id}
122                            bd={ranks[index + 1]?.visible === false ? '0' : undefined}
123                        >
124                            <TableTd>
125                                {ranks[index].visible ?
126                                    ranks[index].text :
127                                    <VisuallyHidden>{ranks[index].text}</VisuallyHidden>}
128                            </TableTd>
129                            <TableTd>
130                                <PlayerLink player={record.player} year={year} />
131                            </TableTd>
132                            <TableTd>
133                                <TableScore table={table} playerRecord={record} />
134                            </TableTd>
135                        </TableTr>
136                    ))}
137                </TableTbody>
138            </Table>
139            {hiddenCount > 0 &&
140                <Button
140                    onClick={toggle}
141                    variant="subtle"
142                    fullWidth
143                    mt="xs"
144                    aria-expanded={opened}
145                    aria-controls={tbodyId}
146                    rightSection={opened ? <IconChevronUp size={16} /> : <IconChevronDown size={16} />}
147                >
148                    {opened ? 'Show less' : `Show ${hiddenCount} more`}
149                </Button>
150            }
151        </Paper>
152    );
153 };
```

Key mechanics:
- **Paper wrapper:** `<Paper p="sm" miw="14rem" maw="24rem" withBorder>` (line 103).
- **Collapse/expand state:** `useDisclosure(false)` from `@mantine/hooks` (line 97), toggled by a Mantine `Button` (`variant="subtle"`, `fullWidth`) whose label switches between `Show less` and `` `Show ${hiddenCount} more` `` and whose `rightSection` swaps a tabler chevron icon up/down.
- **Accessibility wiring:** `useId()` generates `tbodyId`; the button has `aria-expanded={opened}` and `aria-controls={tbodyId}` pointing at the `<TableTbody id={tbodyId}>`.
- **Row cutoff logic:** `visibleRowCount()` (lines 79–87) starts from `config.recordsTableVisibleRows` and extends forward past any tie so a tied rank group isn't split by the fold.

## 2. Turnout table — separate component, NOT a parameterisation of RecordsTable/YearTable

`turnout` is **not** one of the `TableName` enum values, so it cannot be passed into `RecordsTable`/`YearTable`. It's its own simple component:

**File:** `/Volumes/Development/next-www-toastboy/prisma/zod/schemas/enums/TableName.schema.ts`
```ts
export const TableNameSchema = z.enum(['points', 'averages', 'stalwart', 'speedy', 'pub'])
```
(no `turnout` value)

**File:** `/Volumes/Development/next-www-toastboy/src/components/Turnout/Turnout.tsx` (full source, 37 lines):

```tsx
1  import { Table, TableTbody, TableTd, TableTh, TableThead, TableTr } from '@mantine/core';
2  
3  import { TurnoutByYearType } from '@/types';
4  
5  export interface Props {
6      turnout: TurnoutByYearType[],
7  }
8  
9  export const Turnout = ({ turnout }: Props) => {
10     const rows = turnout.sort((a, b) => b.year - a.year).map((t) => (
11         <TableTr key={t.year}>
12             <TableTd>{t.year}</TableTd>
13             <TableTd>{t.gamesPlayed}</TableTd>
14             <TableTd>{t.gamesCancelled}</TableTd>
15             <TableTd>{t.responsesPerGameInitiated.toFixed(1)}</TableTd>
16             <TableTd>{t.yessesPerGameInitiated.toFixed(1)}</TableTd>
17             <TableTd>{t.playersPerGamePlayed.toFixed(1)}</TableTd>
18         </TableTr>
19     ));
20 
21     return (
22         <Table>
23             <TableThead>
23                 <TableTr>
24                     <TableTh>Year</TableTh>
25                     <TableTh>Played</TableTh>
26                     <TableTh>Cancelled</TableTh>
27                     <TableTh>Response Rate</TableTh>
28                     <TableTh>Yes Rate</TableTh>
29                     <TableTh>Turnout Rate</TableTh>
30                 </TableTr>
31             </TableThead>
32             <TableTbody>{rows}</TableTbody>
33         </Table>
34     );
35 };
```

This table has **no Paper wrapper, no collapse/expand, and visible (not hidden) headers** — it's plain Mantine `Table`. It renders one row per year, not per player, so the "show more/less after N historic rows" concept doesn't map onto it the same way (rows here = years, likely few).

There is also a `TurnoutSkeleton` at `/Volumes/Development/next-www-toastboy/src/components/Turnout/TurnoutSkeleton.tsx`.

## 3. Config value for visible rows

**File:** `/Volumes/Development/next-www-toastboy/src/lib/config.ts`
```ts
const rawConfig: ConfigType = {
    ...
    trophyDisplayThreshold: 5,
    recordsTableVisibleRows: 15,   // line 14
};
```

**File:** `/Volumes/Development/next-www-toastboy/src/types/config.ts` (schema/type, line 30 & 44):
```ts
recordsTableVisibleRows: number;              // ConfigType
recordsTableVisibleRows: z.number().int().min(1),  // ConfigSchema
```

There is no equivalent config entry for turnout — it has no row limit/toggle at all.

## 4. Headers visually hidden — commit `f3cda509 SYS-539 Make RecordsTable headers visually hidden`

Only applied to `RecordsTable` (points/averages/stalwart/speedy/pub), not `Turnout`. Diff:

```diff
--- a/src/components/RecordsTable/RecordsTable.tsx
+++ b/src/components/RecordsTable/RecordsTable.tsx
@@ (inside <TableThead>)
-                    <TableTr>
-                        <TableTh>Position</TableTh>
-                        <TableTh>Player</TableTh>
-                        <TableTh>{scoreHeading}</TableTh>
+                    <TableTr bd="0">
+                        <TableTh p={0}><VisuallyHidden>Position</VisuallyHidden></TableTh>
+                        <TableTh p={0}><VisuallyHidden>Player</VisuallyHidden></TableTh>
+                        <TableTh p={0}><VisuallyHidden>{scoreHeading}</VisuallyHidden></TableTh>
```

Mechanism: Mantine's `VisuallyHidden` component (imported from `@mantine/core`, line 15 in current file) wraps each header's text, and the `<TableTh>` cells get `p={0}` with the row given `bd="0"` (no border) so the collapsed/empty header row doesn't add visible padding/border. This is the standard Mantine "screen-reader only" pattern (offscreen absolute positioning), not a raw CSS class. Same pattern is reused within row rendering for hidden tied-rank text (lines 125–127: `<VisuallyHidden>{ranks[index].text}</VisuallyHidden>` when a rank is tied with the previous one).

## 5. Where these are composed on pages

- **Home page (`points`/`averages`/`stalwart` leaders, 3 rows each):**
  `/Volumes/Development/next-www-toastboy/src/app/footy/page.tsx` (lines 12–49) — loops over `[points, averages, stalwart]`, calling `playerRecordService.getTable(table, year, true, 3)` and rendering `<RecordsTable table={table} year={year} records={tableRecords[i]} />` directly (no `title`/`titleOrder` passed, no `YearTable` wrapper).

- **Full table page for any `TableName` (points/averages/stalwart/speedy/pub), with qualified+unqualified split:**
  `/Volumes/Development/next-www-toastboy/src/app/footy/table/[table]/page.tsx` (lines 105–127) — dynamic route `[table]`, validates `table` against `TableNameSchema`, fetches `tableQualified`/`tableUnqualified` via `playerRecordService.getTable(table, year, true|false)`, and renders:
  ```tsx
  <YearTable table={table} year={year} qualified={tableQualified} unqualified={tableUnqualified} />
  ```
  which is `/Volumes/Development/next-www-toastboy/src/components/YearTable/YearTable.tsx` (full source, 41 lines):
  ```tsx
  1  import { Flex, Group } from '@mantine/core';
  2  import type { TableName } from 'prisma/zod/schemas';
  3  
  4  import { RecordsTable } from '@/components/RecordsTable/RecordsTable';
  5  import { UnqualifiedTableName } from '@/lib/tables';
  6  import { PlayerRecordDataType } from '@/types';
  7  
  8  export interface Props {
  9      table: TableName;
  10     year: number;
  11     qualified: PlayerRecordDataType[];
  12     unqualified: PlayerRecordDataType[];
  13 }
  14 
  15 export const YearTable = ({ table, year, qualified, unqualified }: Props) => {
  16     const utn = UnqualifiedTableName(table) ?? null;
  17 
  18     return (
  19         <Flex direction="column" gap="md">
  20             <RecordsTable
  21                 key={`${table}-${year}-qualified`}
  22                 table={table}
  23                 year={year}
  24                 records={qualified}
  25             />
  26             {utn ?
  27                 <Group mt="xl">
  28                     <RecordsTable
  29                         key={`${table}-${year}-unqualified`}
  30                         table={table}
  31                         year={year}
  32                         records={unqualified}
  33                         title={utn}
  34                         titleOrder={4}
  35                     />
  36                 </Group> :
  37                 null
  38             }
  39         </Flex>
  40     );
  41 };
  ```
  `YearTable` is purely a composition wrapper around two `RecordsTable` instances (qualified always shown untitled; unqualified only shown, with a title, for `averages`/`speedy` per `UnqualifiedTableName` in `/Volumes/Development/next-www-toastboy/src/lib/tables.ts`).

- **Turnout page:**
  `/Volumes/Development/next-www-toastboy/src/app/footy/turnout/page.tsx` — server component, fetches `outcomeService.getTurnoutByYear()`, wraps in a plain `<Paper p="xl">` (this Paper predates/is unrelated to your points treatment — it's just page padding, no `withBorder`, no collapse) and renders `<Turnout turnout={turnout} />`. Route reachable via nav link `"/footy/turnout"` in `/Volumes/Development/next-www-toastboy/src/components/NavBarNested/NavBarNested.tsx` (line 88).

### Summary for your edit

If you want turnout to get the same "show more/less after N rows" + `Paper withBorder` treatment as points, you'll need to modify `/Volumes/Development/next-www-toastboy/src/components/Turnout/Turnout.tsx` directly (it's structurally simple — one `Table` with a sorted `rows` map) — there's no shared generic component between them despite the naming similarity of `RecordsTable`/`YearTable`. You could either replicate the `useDisclosure` + `Paper` + `Button` pattern from `RecordsTable.tsx` inline in `Turnout.tsx`, or factor a shared `CollapsibleTable`/`Paper` wrapper component out of `RecordsTable` that both can use — but that refactor doesn't exist yet.

