+                        <TableTh p={0}><VisuallyHidden>Position</VisuallyHidden></TableTh>
+                        <TableTh p={0}><VisuallyHidden>Player</VisuallyHidden></TableTh>
+                        <TableTh p={0}><VisuallyHidden>{scoreHeading}</VisuallyHidden></TableTh>
```

Mechanism: Mantine's `VisuallyHidden` component (imported from `@mantine/core`, line 15 in current file) wraps each header's text, and the `<TableTh>` cells get `p={0}` with the row given `bd="0"` (no border) so the collapsed/empty header row doesn't add visible padding/border. This is the standard Mantine "screen-reader only" pattern (offscreen absolute positioning), not a raw CSS class. Same pattern is reused within row rendering for hidden tied-rank text (lines 125–127: `<VisuallyHidden>{ranks[index].text}</VisuallyHidden>` when a rank is tied with the previous one).

## 5. Where these are composed on pages

- **Home page (`points`/`averages`/`stalwart` leaders, 3 rows each):**
  `/Volumes/Development/next-www-toastboy/src/app/footy/page.tsx` (lines 12–49) — loops over `[points, averages, stalwart]`, calling `playerRecordService.getTable(table, year, true, 3)` and rendering `<RecordsTable table={table} year={year} records={tableRecords[i]} />` directly (no `title`/`titleOrder` passed, no `YearTable` wrapper).

- **Full table page for any `TableName` (points/averages/stalwart/speedy/pub), with qualified+unqualified split:**
  `/Volumes/Development/next-www-toastboy/src/app/footy/table/[table]/page.tsx` (lines 105–127) — dynamic route `[table]`, validates `table` against `TableNameSchema`, fetches `tableQualified`/`tableUnqualified` via `playerRecordService.getTable(table, year, true|false)`, and renders:
  ```tsx
  <YearTable table={table} year={year} qualified={tableQualified} unqualified={tableUnqualified} />
  ```
  which is `/Volumes/Development/next-www-toastboy/src/components/YearTable/YearTable.tsx` (full source, 41 lines):
  ```tsx
  1  import { Flex, Group } from '@mantine/core';
  2  import type { TableName } from 'prisma/zod/schemas';
  3  
  4  import { RecordsTable } from '@/components/RecordsTable/RecordsTable';
  5  import { UnqualifiedTableName } from '@/lib/tables';
  6  import { PlayerRecordDataType } from '@/types';
  7  
  8  export interface Props {
  9      table: TableName;
  10     year: number;
  11     qualified: PlayerRecordDataType[];
  12     unqualified: PlayerRecordDataType[];
  13 }
  14 
  15 export const YearTable = ({ table, year, qualified, unqualified }: Props) => {
  16     const utn = UnqualifiedTableName(table) ?? null;
  17 
  18     return (
  19         <Flex direction="column" gap="md">
  20             <RecordsTable
  21                 key={`${table}-${year}-qualified`}
  22                 table={table}
  23                 year={year}
  24                 records={qualified}
  25             />
  26             {utn ?
  27                 <Group mt="xl">
  28                     <RecordsTable
  29                         key={`${table}-${year}-unqualified`}
  30                         table={table}
  31                         year={year}
  32                         records={unqualified}
  33                         title={utn}
  34                         titleOrder={4}
  35                     />
  36                 </Group> :
  37                 null
  38             }
  39         </Flex>
  40     );
  41 };
  ```
  `YearTable` is purely a composition wrapper around two `RecordsTable` instances (qualified always shown untitled; unqualified only shown, with a title, for `averages`/`speedy` per `UnqualifiedTableName` in `/Volumes/Development/next-www-toastboy/src/lib/tables.ts`).

- **Turnout page:**
  `/Volumes/Development/next-www-toastboy/src/app/footy/turnout/page.tsx` — server component, fetches `outcomeService.getTurnoutByYear()`, wraps in a plain `<Paper p="xl">` (this Paper predates/is unrelated to your points treatment — it's just page padding, no `withBorder`, no collapse) and renders `<Turnout turnout={turnout} />`. Route reachable via nav link `"/footy/turnout"` in `/Volumes/Development/next-www-toastboy/src/components/NavBarNested/NavBarNested.tsx` (line 88).

### Summary for your edit

If you want turnout to get the same "show more/less after N rows" + `Paper withBorder` treatment as points, you'll need to modify `/Volumes/Development/next-www-toastboy/src/components/Turnout/Turnout.tsx` directly (it's structurally simple — one `Table` with a sorted `rows` map) — there's no shared generic component between them despite the naming similarity of `RecordsTable`/`YearTable`. You could either replicate the `useDisclosure` + `Paper` + `Button` pattern from `RecordsTable.tsx` inline in `Turnout.tsx`, or factor a shared `CollapsibleTable`/`Paper` wrapper component out of `RecordsTable` that both can use — but that refactor doesn't exist yet.

